 Engagement & Learning:\n- Peakon Aps\n- Performancepro\n- Epignosis Llc\n\nGROUP 18 - Corporate Secretarial:\n- Acclime Corporate Services\n- Acclime Usa, Inc\n- Intertrust Singapore Corporate Services Pte Ltd - Csc\n\nGROUP 19 - Workflow Automation:\n- Workato, Inc.\n- Zapier Inc.\n\nGROUP 20 - Developer Tools & Monitoring:\n- Jetbrains S.R.O.\n- Papertrail Inc\n- Solarwinds, Inc\n\nGROUP 21 - Apple Hardware (Multi-Entity):\n- Apple Retail Uk Ltd\n- Apple Pty Ltd\n- Apple Distribution International Ltd\n- Apple - Amer\n\nGROUP 22 - Allianz Insurance (Duplicate):\n- Allianz Australia Workers' Compensation (Victoria) Limited\n- Allianz Wa\n\nGROUP 23 - Occupational Health Croatia:\n- Specijalisticka Ordinacija Medicine Rada Helena Blazic\n- Specijalisticka Ordinacija Medicine Rada I Sporta Ina Kardos\n- Ustanova Za Medicinu Rada I Sporta Dr. Novacki\n- Ustanova Za Zdravstvenu Skrb P.P.\n\nFor each group, print:\nGROUP_NUMBER | GROUP_NAME | TOTAL_SPEND_USD | VENDOR_COUNT\nAlso print the GRAND_TOTAL across all 23 groups.\n\nRun the script and return the output.","agentId":"a0e33eaa616ad6d2a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 23 groups matched perfectly — zero unmatched vendors. Here are the results:\n\n---\n\n**GROUP | GROUP NAME | TOTAL_SPEND_USD | VENDOR_COUNT**\n\n| # | Group Name | Total Spend (USD) | Vendors |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | CRM & Sales Engagement | $3,156,660.40 | 5 |\n| 2 | Office Space & Real Estate | $827,833.50 | 8 |\n| 3 | Travel & Expense (Navan) | $415,912.91 | 2 |\n| 4 | Audit & Accounting | $412,219.19 | 5 |\n| 5 | Cloud Infrastructure | $390,710.41 | 5 |\n| 6 | Employee Health Insurance | $238,406.18 | 10 |\n| 7 | Financial & M&A Advisory | $226,932.25 | 4 |\n| 8 | HR Outsourcing & Payroll | $161,707.66 | 5 |\n| 9 | Marketing Automation & Digital Advertising | $161,420.08 | 6 |\n| 10 | Insurance Brokerage | $152,800.20 | 2 |\n| 11 | Telecoms & Connectivity | $147,711.78 | 8 |\n| 12 | Financial Planning SaaS | $127,461.57 | 3 |\n| 13 | Recruitment & Staffing | $121,014.48 | 5 |\n| 14 | Legal Services | $112,553.52 | 13 |\n| 15 | 4I Advisory (Duplicate Entities) | $83,977.83 | 2 |\n| 16 | Work Management Tools | $76,023.82 | 4 |\n| 17 | Employee Engagement & Learning | $27,958.60 | 3 |\n| 18 | Corporate Secretarial | $17,767.48 | 3 |\n| 19 | Workflow Automation | $16,267.81 | 2 |\n| 20 | Developer Tools & Monitoring | $8,148.80 | 3 |\n| 21 | Apple Hardware (Multi-Entity) | $8,256.02 | 4 |\n| 22 | Allianz Insurance (Duplicate) | $7,069.34 | 2 |\n| 23 | Occupational Health Croatia | $191.67 | 4 |\n| **GRAND TOTAL** | | **$6,899,005.49** | **118 vendor entries** |\n\n**Key observations:**\n\n- Every vendor name matched exactly — no unresolved lookups.\n- Group 1 (CRM) dominates at $3.16M, representing 45.8% of the grand total on its own.\n- Group 22 (Allianz Insurance Duplicate) is a subset of Group 6 (Employee Health Insurance) — the two Allianz entities ($7,069.34) are already counted within Group 6's $238,406.18 total, so the grand total double-counts them by $7,069.34 if Groups 6 and 22 are both used independently.\n- The grand total of $6,899,005.49 is slightly higher than the $6.23M previously noted in project memory (STEP 07), likely because this run includes all 23 groups including the duplicate Allianz group."}],"totalDurationMs":91953,"totalTokens":16644,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2740,"cache_read_input_tokens":13044,"output_tokens":859,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2740},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W7XQ2UGK12RzxdW1VKvQmt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the precise spend totals. Note the agent flagged that Group 22 (Allianz) is a subset of Group 6, so there's a $7,069.34 double-count. The true grand total without the double-count would be $6,899,005.49 - $7,069.34 = $6,891,936.15. But for the output, I'll present all 23 groups and note that Groups 6 and 22 overlap slightly.\n\nActually, let me reconsider the structure. Since the occupational health vendors in Group 23 ($191) are NOT in Group 6 (they're different from Allianz), the only double-count is the Allianz Insurance entities appearing in both Group 6 and Group 22.\n\n\nFor the output, I'll present all 23 groups with the category, vendors, combined spend, and consolidation candidates. I need to decide whether to remove the Allianz entities from Group 6 entirely, remove Group 22 and just flag Allianz as a consolidation candidate within Group 6, or keep both and clarify the overlap. The cleanest approach is probably to remove Group 22 and note Allianz as a consolidation candidate within Group 6 to avoid the double-count in the final totals.\n\nActually, I'll keep all 23 groups as defined and just note in Group 6 that Allianz entities are also flagged separately. The combined spend per group is accurate, and the grand total will have a small $7K double-count that I can acknowledge. Now I'll write out the full table and update the memory file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":47941,"cache_read_input_tokens":6212,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":47941,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ed88350-d5e8-4179-8856-45e53162fa46","uuid":"5b0872da-9d55-4a81-