{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W7XQ2UGK12RzxdW1VKvQmt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015qFB917zGn59viyQ8hupNi","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\rjega\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-rjega-vendor-spend-analysis\\memory\\project_step07_consolidation.md","content":"---\nname: STEP 07 Consolidation Analysis\ndescription: STEP 07 consolidation analysis: 23 opportunity groups, ~$6.89M combined spend in scope across 4 priority tiers; CRM ($3.16M) is #1; use in STEP 09\ntype: project\n---\n\n23 consolidation opportunity groups identified across 118 vendor entries, $6,899,005 combined spend (note: Allianz $7,069 counted in both Group 6 and Group 22; adjusted unique spend ~$6,892K).\n\n## Priority Tier 1 — >$200K (Groups 1–7)\n\n| # | Category | Combined Spend | Key Vendors | Action |\n|---|----------|---------------|-------------|--------|\n| 1 | CRM & Sales Engagement | $3,156,660 | Salesforce UK ($3,117,226), Cognism ($27,013), Outreach Corp ($9,206), Lusha ($2,606), D&B ($610) | Retain Salesforce; consolidate Cognism/Outreach/Lusha into Salesforce-native tools or single sales-intelligence vendor |\n| 2 | Office Space & Real Estate | $827,834 | TOG UK ($263,821), Zagrebtower ($183,754), Innovent Spaces ($147,348), GPT Space ($133,507), WeWork SG ($64,373), JLL ($16,274), Work Easy ($14,913), Common Desk ($3,842) | Appoint JLL as single real estate manager; rationalize co-working agreements; exit underutilised flex sites |\n| 3 | Travel & Expense (Navan duplicate) | $415,913 | Navan/Tripactions ($357,984), Navan Inc ($57,929) | IMMEDIATE: same vendor, two billing entities — consolidate to single Navan contract |\n| 4 | Audit & Accounting | $412,219 | BDO LLP ($343,081), Grant Thornton ($46,539), Granttree ($13,659), PwC ($4,879), Crowe Horwath ($4,062) | Retain BDO as primary statutory auditor; consolidate advisory to BDO; keep Granttree for R&D credits only |\n| 5 | Cloud Infrastructure | $390,710 | Cloudcrossing ($208,675), AWS LLC ($106,399), Cloud Technology Solutions ($60,661), Microsoft Ireland ($9,822), AWS Inc ($5,153) | Consolidate AWS LLC + Inc to single contract (duplicate entity); clarify Cloudcrossing role vs native AWS; define AWS vs Azure strategy |\n| 6 | Employee Health Insurance | $238,406 | Aetna ($124,661), Agram Life ($24,952), Care Health ($24,045), Bupa Supplier ($22,800), Cigna SG ($13,249), Bupa Australia ($12,463), Allianz AU ($6,099), ICICI Lombard ($5,972), Cici Prudential ($3,195), Allianz WA ($971) | Merge Bupa Supplier + Bupa Australia; merge Allianz AU + WA (see Group 22); engage global benefits broker for coordination |\n| 7 | Financial & M&A Advisory | $226,932 | RSM UK Corporate Finance ($117,078), SS&C Intralinks ($39,966), Houlihan Lokey ($37,461), Vector Capital ($32,427) | Project-based; consolidate VDR to SS&C Intralinks; rationalize M&A advisors to preferred panel |\n\n## Priority Tier 2 — $100K–$200K (Groups 8–14)\n\n| # | Category | Combined Spend | Key Vendors | Action |\n|---|----------|---------------|-------------|--------|\n| 8 | HR Outsourcing & Payroll | $161,708 | HR Solution GmbH ($80,823), Harmonic Group ($65,418), HRSolution AG ($6,987), Mercer ($5,444), NCC Services ($3,036) | Consolidate HRSolution GmbH + AG (same brand, two legal entities); evaluate Harmonic vs HRSolution geographic overlap; target single global HR/payroll provider |\n| 9 | Marketing Automation & Digital Advertising | $161,420 | LinkedIn Ireland ($55,573), HubSpot Ireland ($32,187), Uberflip ($26,091), Google Ireland ($24,798), MightyHive ($19,042), Semrush ($3,730) | Retain HubSpot as primary; evaluate Uberflip vs HubSpot Content Hub (eliminate overlap); rationalise MightyHive as agency layer |\n| 10 | Insurance Brokerage | $152,800 | Jensten Insurance Brokers ($142,700), Shoff Darby Companies ($10,100) | Consolidate to single broker; Jensten as primary |\n| 11 | Telecoms & Connectivity | $147,712 | Telefonica Global ($89,880), New Star Networks ($23,887), Hrvatski Telekom ($18,084), Telemach Hrvatska ($5,134), Vodafone AU ($3,672), T-Mobile ($3,357), Starhub ($2,205), British Telecom ($1,493) | Retain Telefonica as global primary; rationalise Croatian connectivity (Hrvatski vs Telemach); consolidate mobile contracts by region |\n| 12 | Financial Planning SaaS | $127,462 | Kimble Applications ($52,825), Sage UK ($46,895), Planful ($27,741) | Retain Sage for statutory accounting; evaluate Kimble (PSA) vs Planful (FP&A) for overlap; consolidate finance planning to one platform |\n| 13 | Recruitment & Staffing Agencies | $121,014 | Accutrainee ($38,841), Mason Frank ($38,148), Technet IT ($21,952), Cedar Recruitment ($18,537), Info Edge India ($3,536) | Establish preferred supplier list of 2–3 agencies; Mason Frank for Salesforce roles; phase out casual agency usage |\n| 14 | Legal Services | $112,554 | Bisley Law ($67,414), Eurofast ($18,164), Visalogic ($11,241), Virtual Legal Counsel ($4,800), Pinsent Masons ($4,078), others (~$6,858) | Consolidate to 3-firm panel: Bisley (employment), Pinsent Masons (commercial/tech), Visalogic (immigration) |\n\n## Priority Tier 3 — $25K–$100K (Groups 15–17)\n\n| # | Category | Combined Spend | Key Vendors | Action |\n|---|----------|---------------|-------------|--------|\n| 15 | 4I Advisory (Duplicate Entities) | $83,978 | 4I Advisory Services ($71,860), 4I Management Consulting PL ($12,117) | Same parent brand, two legal registrations — consolidate to single master services agreement |\n| 16 | Work Management & Project Tools | $76,024 | Monday.com/Big Frontier ($66,131), Trello ($6,674), Smartsheet ($2,995), Atlassian ($224) | Standardise on Monday.com; terminate Trello and Smartsheet |\n| 17 | Employee Engagement & Learning | $27,959 | Peakon APS ($17,108), PerformancePro ($10,018), Epignosis ($833) | Consolidate to single employee engagement + performance platform; Peakon preferred |\n\n## Priority Tier 4 — <$25K (Groups 18–23)\n\n| # | Category | Combined Spend | Key Vendors | Action |\n|---|----------|---------------|-------------|--------|\n| 18 | Corporate Secretarial / Entity Mgmt | $17,768 | Acclime Corporate Services ($5,413), Acclime USA ($4,995), Intertrust Singapore ($7,360) | Consolidate Acclime entities to single global contract; retain Intertrust for Singapore |\n| 19 | Workflow Automation | $16,268 | Workato ($16,101), Zapier ($167) | Retain Workato for enterprise automation; terminate Zapier |\n| 20 | Developer Tools & Monitoring | $8,149 | JetBrains ($4,083), Papertrail ($3,900), Solarwinds ($166) | Retain JetBrains + Papertrail; assess whether Solarwinds overlaps with Papertrail |\n| 21 | Apple Hardware (Multi-Entity) | $8,256 | Apple Retail UK ($3,548), Apple Pty ($2,031), Apple Distribution Int'l ($1,913), Apple AMER ($764) | Consolidate Apple procurement through Apple Business Manager or single authorised reseller |\n| 22 | Allianz Insurance (Duplicate Entities) | $7,069 | Allianz Australia Workers' Comp ($6,099), Allianz WA ($971) | Sub-group of Group 6: same insurer, two state entities — consolidate to single Allianz national policy |\n| 23 | Occupational Health Croatia (Duplicates) | $192 | Spec. Ordinacija Helena Blazic ($20), Spec. Ordinacija Ina Kardos ($20), Ustanova Medicina Rada Dr. Novacki ($20), Ustanova Zdravstvenu Skrb ($131) | Consolidate to single occupational health provider in Croatia |\n\n## Top-3 Pre-Sized Opportunities for STEP 09\n\n1. **CRM & Sales Engagement** — $3,156,660: Salesforce is non-negotiable; Cognism + Outreach + Lusha are ~$39K of overlap spend that could be eliminated if Salesforce Sales Intelligence features cover the use case.\n2. **Office Space & Real Estate** — $827,834: Engagement with JLL as strategic broker could yield 10–20% renegotiation savings (~$83–165K) across TOG, GPT, and Innovent.\n3. **Travel & Expense (Navan duplicate)** — $415,913: Zero-effort consolidation; two billing entities for same vendor. Estimated savings from single contract renegotiation: 5–10% (~$21–42K).\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":47941,"cache_read_input_tokens":6212,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":47941,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ed88350-d5e8-4179-8856-45e53162fa46","uuid":"481141fe-b203-401e-abd0-41892d07b14d"}
