WeWork SG ($64,373) + JLL ($16,274) + Work Easy ($14,913) + Common Desk ($3,842)\n   - Appoint JLL as strategic real estate manager; rationalise co-working agreements; exit underutilised flex sites\n\n3. **Travel & Expense — Navan Duplicate** — $415,913\n   - Navan/TripActions Inc ($357,984) + Navan Inc ($57,929)\n   - IMMEDIATE: same vendor, two AP entities — consolidate to single Navan contract; renegotiate on combined $416K volume\n\n4. **Audit & Accounting** — $412,219\n   - BDO LLP ($343,081) + Grant Thornton ($46,539) + Granttree ($13,659) + PwC ($4,879) + Crowe Horwath ($4,062)\n   - Retain BDO as primary statutory auditor; consolidate advisory to BDO; retain Granttree for R&D credits only\n\n5. **Cloud Infrastructure** — $390,710\n   - Cloudcrossing BVBA ($208,675) + AWS LLC ($106,399) + Cloud Technology Solutions ($60,661) + Microsoft Ireland ($9,822) + AWS Inc. ($5,153)\n   - Consolidate AWS LLC + Inc to single contract (duplicate entity); clarify Cloudcrossing scope vs native AWS; define AWS vs Azure strategy\n\n6. **Employee Health Insurance** — $238,406\n   - Aetna ($124,661) + Agram Life ($24,952) + Care Health ($24,045) + Bupa-Supplier ($22,800) + Cigna SG ($13,249) + Bupa Australia ($12,463) + Allianz AU ($6,099) + ICICI Lombard ($5,972) + Cici Prudential ($3,195) + Allianz WA ($971)\n   - Merge Bupa Supplier + Bupa Australia; merge Allianz AU + WA entities (see Group 22); engage global benefits broker for coordination\n\n7. **Financial & M&A Advisory** — $226,932\n   - RSM UK Corporate Finance ($117,078) + SS&C Intralinks ($39,966) + Houlihan Lokey ($37,461) + Vector Capital ($32,427)\n   - Project-based; consolidate VDR to SS&C Intralinks; rationalise M&A advisors to preferred panel; verify ongoing need post-deal\n\n---\n\n## Priority Tier 2 — Combined Spend $100K–$200K (Groups 8–14, ~$983,872)\n\n8. **HR Outsourcing & Payroll** — $161,708\n   - HR Solution GmbH ($80,823) + Harmonic Group ($65,418) + HRSolution AG ($6,987) + Mercer ($5,444) + NCC Services ($3,036)\n   - Consolidate HRSolution GmbH + AG (same brand, two legal entities); evaluate Harmonic vs HRSolution geographic overlap; target single global HR/payroll provider\n\n9. **Marketing Automation & Digital Advertising** — $161,420\n   - LinkedIn Ireland ($55,573) + HubSpot Ireland ($32,187) + Uberflip ($26,091) + Google Ireland ($24,798) + MightyHive ($19,042) + Semrush ($3,730)\n   - Retain HubSpot as primary; evaluate Uberflip vs HubSpot Content Hub (eliminate overlap); rationalise MightyHive as agency layer\n\n10. **Insurance Brokerage** — $152,800\n    - Jensten Insurance Brokers ($142,700) + Shoff Darby Companies ($10,100)\n    - Consolidate to single broker; Jensten as primary; negotiate combined policy portfolio discount\n\n11. **Telecoms & Connectivity** — $147,712\n    - Telefonica Global ($89,880) + New Star Networks ($23,887) + Hrvatski Telekom ($18,084) + Telemach Hrvatska ($5,134) + Vodafone AU ($3,672) + T-Mobile ($3,357) + Starhub ($2,205) + British Telecom ($1,493)\n    - Retain Telefonica Global as primary; rationalise Croatian connectivity (Hrvatski vs Telemach); consolidate mobile contracts by region\n\n12. **Financial Planning SaaS** — $127,462\n    - Kimble Applications ($52,825) + Sage UK ($46,895) + Planful ($27,741)\n    - Retain Sage for statutory accounting; evaluate Kimble (PSA) vs Planful (FP&A) for overlap; consolidate finance planning to one platform\n\n13. **Recruitment & Staffing Agencies** — $121,014\n    - Accutrainee ($38,841) + Mason Frank ($38,148) + Technet IT ($21,952) + Cedar Recruitment ($18,537) + Info Edge India ($3,536)\n    - Establish preferred supplier list of 2–3 agencies; Mason Frank for Salesforce roles; phase out casual agency usage\n\n14. **Legal Services** — $112,554\n    - Bisley Law ($67,414) + Eurofast International ($18,164) + Visalogic ($11,241) + Virtual Legal Counsel ($4,800) + Pinsent Masons ($4,078) + others ($6,858)\n    - Consolidate to 3-firm panel: Bisley (employment), Pinsent Masons (commercial/tech), Visalogic (immigration); exit remaining 10 small firms\n\n---\n\n## Priority Tier 3 — Combined Spend $25K–$100K (Groups 15–17, ~$187,960)\n\n15. **4I Advisory — Duplicate Entities** — $83,978\n    - 4I Advisory Services ($71,860) + 4I Management Consulting PL ($12,117)\n    - Same parent brand, two legal registrations — consolidate to single master services agreement\n\n16. **Work Management & Project Tools** — $76,024\n    - Monday.com/Big Frontier ($66,131) + Trello ($6,674) + Smartsheet ($2,995) + Atlassian ($224)\n    - Standardise on Monday.com; terminate Trello and Smartsheet; roll Atlassian ($224) into Monday.com enterprise plan\n\n17. **Employee Engagement & Learning** — $27,959\n    - Peakon APS ($17,108) + PerformancePro ($10,018) + Epignosis ($833)\n    - Consolidate to single employee engagement + performance platform; Peakon preferred; evaluate Epignosis vs internal LMS\n\n---\n\n## Priority Tier 4 — Combined Spend < $25K (Groups 18–23, ~$58,271)\n\n18. **Corporate Secretarial / Entity Mgmt** — $17,768\n    - Acclime Corporate Services ($5,413) + Acclime USA ($4,995) + Intertrust Singapore ($7,360)\n    - Consolidate Acclime entities to single global contract; retain Intertrust for Singapore-specific compliance\n\n19. **Workflow Automation** — $16,268\n    - Workato Inc. ($16,101) + Zapier Inc. ($167)\n    - Retain Workato (enterprise iPaaS); migrate Zapier automations to Workato; terminate Zapier\n\n20. **Developer Tools & Monitoring** — $8,149\n    - JetBrains ($4,083) + Papertrail ($3,900) + Solarwinds ($166)\n    - Retain JetBrains + Papertrail; assess Solarwinds overlap with Papertrail; consolidate if duplicated\n\n21. **Apple Hardware — Multi-Entity** — $8,256\n    - Apple Retail UK ($3,548) + Apple Pty ($2,031) + Apple Distribution Int'l ($1,913) + Apple AMER ($764)\n    - Consolidate all four to single Apple Business Manager account; single contract for hardware purchasing\n\n22. **Allianz Insurance — Duplicate Entities** — $7,069\n    - Allianz Australia Workers' Comp ($6,099) + Allianz WA ($971)\n    - Sub-group within Group 6: same insurer, two state policy accounts — merge WA into national Allianz account\n\n23. **Occupational Health Croatia — Duplicate Clinics** — $192\n    - Specijalisticka Ordinacija Helena Blazic ($20) + Specijalisticka Ordinacija Ina Kardos ($20) + Ustanova Medicina Rada Dr. Novacki ($20) + Ustanova Zdravstvenu Skrb ($131)\n    - Designate single occupational health provider in Croatia; terminate others\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table for Step 09\n\n| Priority | Groups | Combined Spend |\n|---|---|---|\n| P1 (≥$200K) | 7 | $5,668,677 |\n| P2 ($100K–$200K) | 7 | $983,872 |\n| P3 ($25K–$100K) | 3 | $187,960 |\n| P4 (<$25K) | 6 | $58,271 |\n| **TOTAL** | **23** | **~$6,899,005** |\n\nKey insight for Step 09: CRM alone = $3.16M (45.8% of in-scope spend). Duplicate AP entity cleanup (Navan, HRSolution, Acclime, AWS, Bupa, Allianz, Apple, DHL) = ~$110K zero-negotiation savings from AP hygiene alone.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":132,"newStart":1,"newLines":132,"lines":[" ---"," name: STEP 07 Consolidation Opportunity Analysis","-description: STEP 07 results - 23 duplicate vendor category groups across 4 priority tiers, ~$6.23M spend in scope; CRM is #1 at $3.15M; use in STEP 09 strategy recommendations","+description: STEP 07 consolidation analysis: 23 opportunity groups, ~$6.89M combined spend in scope across 4 priority tiers; CRM ($3.16M) is #1; use in STEP 09 strategy recommendations"," type: project"," ---"," ","-STEP 07 identified 23 consolidation opportunity groups. Total spend in scope: ~$6,226,935 across 386 vendors.","+STEP 07 identified 23 consolidation opportunity groups across 118 vendor entries. Total spend in scope: ~$6,899,005 (note: Allianz $7,069 counted in both Group 6 and Group 22; adjusted ~$6,892K unique spend)."," "," **Why:** Vendor master has duplicate AP entities, same-vendor product overlap, functional platform duplication, and unchecked agency/office proliferation.","-**How to apply:** Reference these groups in STEP 09 strategy recommendations. P1 groups (>=200K) are immediate CFO-level actions; P2/P3 feed the 90-day vendor review roadmap; P4 is hygiene cleanup.","+**How to apply:** Reference these groups in STEP 09 strategy recommendations. P1 groups (≥$200K) are immediate CFO-level actions; P2/P3 feed the 90-day vendor review roadmap; P4 is hygiene cleanup."," "," ---"," ","-## Priority 1 — Combined Spend ≥ $200K (6 groups, ~$5,401,697)","+## Priority Tier 1 — Combined Spend ≥ $200K (Groups 1–7, ~$5,668,677)"," ","-1. **CRM & Marketing Automation** — $3,151,402","-   - Salesforce UK ($3,117,226) + HubSpot Ireland ($32,187) + Slack Technologies ($1,989)","-   - Retain Salesforce; consolidate Slack via Salesforce EA; evaluate HubSpot overlap with Salesforce Marketing Cloud","+1. **CRM & Sales Engagement** — $3,156,660","+   - Salesforce UK ($3,117,226) + Cognism ($27,013) + Outreach Corp ($9,206) + Lusha ($2,606) + D&B ($610)","+   - Retain Salesforce; consolidate Cognism/Outreach/Lusha into Salesforce-native tools or single sales-intelligence vendor; ~$39K overlap spend to eliminate"," ","-2. **Flexible Office Space / Coworking** — $955,652","-   - TOG UK ($263,821) + Zagrebtower ($183,754) + Innovent Spaces ($147,348) + Weking ($144,093) + GPT Space ($133,507) + WeWork Singapore ($64,373) + Work Easy ($14,913) + Common Desk ($3,842)","-   - Retain TOG (London), Innovent (India), Zagrebtower (Croatia) as regional anchors; exit GPT Space, WeWork, Weking, Work Easy, Common Desk","+2. **Office Space & Real Estate** — $827,834","+   - TOG UK ($263,821) + Zagrebtower ($183,754) + Innovent Spaces ($147,348) + GPT Space ($133,507) + WeWork SG ($64,373) + JLL ($16,274) + Work Easy ($14,913) + Common Desk ($3,842)","+   - Appoint JLL as strategic real estate manager; rationalise co-working agreements; exit underutilised flex sites"," ","-3. **Audit, Accounting & Finance Advisory** — $533,422","-   - BDO LLP ($343,081) + RSM UK Corporate Finance ($117,078) + Grant Thornton ($46,539) + Collards ($12,879) + PwC ($4,879) + Crowe Horwath ($4,062) + McBurneys ($2,711) + N S Shastri ($2,194)","-   - Retain BDO (primary) + RSM (secondary); redirect all other firms to BDO/RSM panel; terminate standalone smaller firms","+3. **Travel & Expense — Navan Duplicate** — $415,913","+   - Navan/TripActions Inc ($357,984) + Navan Inc ($57,929)","+   - IMMEDIATE: same vendor, two AP entities — consolidate to single Navan contract; renegotiate on combined $416K volume"," ","-4. **T&E Platform — Navan Duplicate** — $415,913","-   - Navan (TripActions Inc) ($357,984) + Navan Inc ($57,929)","-   - Same vendor, two AP entities; merge Navan Inc into TripActions master; renegotiate on combined $416K volume","+4. **Audit & Accounting** — $412,219","+   - BDO LLP ($343,081) + Grant Thornton ($46,539) + Granttree ($13,659) + PwC ($4,879) + Crowe Horwath ($4,062)","+   - Retain BDO as primary statutory auditor; consolidate advisory to BDO; retain Granttree for R&D credits only"," ","-5. **Cloud Infrastructure** — $415,508","-   - Cloudcrossing BVBA ($208,675) + AWS LLC ($106,399) + Cloud Technology Solutions ($60,661) + Google Ireland ($24,798) + Microsoft Ireland ($9,822) + AWS Inc. ($5,153)","-   - Merge AWS Inc. into AWS LLC org billing; evaluate CTS vs Cloudcrossing scope overlap; audit Azure vs AWS allocation","+5. **Cloud Infrastructure** — $390,710","+   - Cloudcrossing BVBA ($208,675) + AWS LLC ($106,399) + Cloud Technology Solutions ($60,661) + Microsoft Ireland ($9,822) + AWS Inc. ($5,153)","+   - Consolidate AWS LLC + Inc to single contract (duplicate entity); clarify Cloudcrossing scope vs native AWS; define AWS vs Azure strategy"," ","-6. **Group Health Insurance** — $339,918","-   - Aetna Life & Casualty ($124,661) + Jensten Insurance ($142,700) + Care Health ($24,045) + Bupa-Supplier ($22,800) + Cigna SG ($13,249) + Bupa Australia ($12,463)","-   - Consolidate Bupa Australia into Bupa-Supplier; benchmark Aetna at renewal; rationalise to max 2–3 global providers","+6. **Employee Health Insurance** — $238,406","+   - Aetna ($124,661) + Agram Life ($24,952) + Care Health ($24,045) + Bupa-Supplier ($22,800) + Cigna SG ($13,249) + Bupa Australia ($12,463) + Allianz AU ($6,099) + ICICI Lombard ($5,972) + Cici Prudential ($3,195) + Allianz WA ($971)","+   - Merge Bupa Supplier + Bupa Australia; merge Allianz AU + WA entities (see Group 22); engage global benefits broker for coordination"," ","+7. **Financial & M&A Advisory** — $226,932","+   - RSM UK Corporate Finance ($117,078) + SS&C Intralinks ($39,966) + Houlihan Lokey ($37,461) + Vector Capital ($32,427)","+   - Project-based; consolidate VDR to SS&C Intralinks; rationalise M&A advisors to preferred panel; verify ongoing need post-deal","+"," ---"," ","-## Priority 2 — Combined Spend $50K–$200K (6 groups, ~$573,765)","+## Priority Tier 2 — Combined Spend $100K–$200K (Groups 8–14, ~$983,872)"," ","-7. **Telecom & Connectivity** — $129,982","-   - Telefonica Global Services GmbH ($89,880) + Hrvatski Telekom ($18,084) + Telefonica Compras Electronicas ($6,157) + Telemach Hrvatska ($5,134) + Vodafone AU ($3,672) + T-Mobile ($3,357) + Starhub ($2,205) + British Telecom ($1,493)","-   - Retain Telefonica Global GmbH as primary; merge Telefonica Compras into GmbH; retain regional carriers only where no Telefonica coverage","+8. **HR Outsourcing & Payroll** — $161,708","+   - HR Solution GmbH ($80,823) + Harmonic Group ($65,418) + HRSolution AG ($6,987) + Mercer ($5,444) + NCC Services ($3,036)","+   - Consolidate HRSolution GmbH + AG (same brand, two legal entities); evaluate Harmonic vs HRSolution geographic overlap; target single global HR/payroll provider"," ","-8. **M&A Advisory & Deal Services** — $109,854","-   - SS&C Intralinks ($39,966) + Houlihan Lokey ($37,461) + Vector Capital ($32,427)","-   - Deal-specific spend; verify ongoing engagement; terminate post-deal if activity complete","+9. **Marketing Automation & Digital Advertising** — $161,420","+   - LinkedIn Ireland ($55,573) + HubSpot Ireland ($32,187) + Uberflip ($26,091) + Google Ireland ($24,798) + MightyHive ($19,042) + Semrush ($3,730)","+   - Retain HubSpot as primary; evaluate Uberflip vs HubSpot Content Hub (eliminate overlap); rationalise MightyHive as agency layer"," ","-9. **Digital & Performance Marketing Agencies** — $102,247","-   - Big Frontier/Cult of Monday ($66,131) + Mightyhive ($19,042) + Plus Your Business ($17,074)","-   - Retain Big Frontier as lead agency; consolidate Mightyhive + Plus Your Business mandates into Big Frontier","+10. **Insurance Brokerage** — $152,800","+    - Jensten Insurance Brokers ($142,700) + Shoff Darby Companies ($10,100)","+    - Consolidate to single broker; Jensten as primary; negotiate combined policy portfolio discount"," ","-10. **HR Services — Duplicate Entity** — $87,810","-    - HR Solution International GmbH ($80,823) + HRsolution International AG ($6,987)","-    - Same vendor, two legal entities; merge AG into GmbH master agreement","+11. **Telecoms & Connectivity** — $147,712","+    - Telefonica Global ($89,880) + New Star Networks ($23,887) + Hrvatski Telekom ($18,084) + Telemach Hrvatska ($5,134) + Vodafone AU ($3,672) + T-Mobile ($3,357) + Starhub ($2,205) + British Telecom ($1,493)","+    - Retain Telefonica Global as primary; rationalise Croatian connectivity (Hrvatski vs Telemach); consolidate mobile contracts by region"," ","-11. **Sales Intelligence & Prospecting** — $85,801","-    - LinkedIn Ireland ($55,573) + Cognism ($27,013) + Lusha ($2,606) + Dun & Bradstreet ($610)","-    - Retain LinkedIn + Cognism; terminate Lusha and D&B (overlapping, lower-tier tools)","+12. **Financial Planning SaaS** — $127,462","+    - Kimble Applications ($52,825) + Sage UK ($46,895) + Planful ($27,741)","+    - Retain Sage for statutory accounting; evaluate Kimble (PSA) vs Planful (FP&A) for overlap; consolidate finance planning to one platform"," ","-12. **TM Forum — Duplicate AP Entry** — $58,071","-    - Tmforum ($57,560) + Tm Forum ($510)","-    - Same association, duplicate AP records; deduplicate to single entry immediately","+13. **Recruitment & Staffing Agencies** — $121,014","+    - Accutrainee ($38,841) + Mason Frank ($38,148) + Technet IT ($21,952) + Cedar Recruitment ($18,537) + Info Edge India ($3,536)","+    - Establish preferred supplier list of 2–3 agencies; Mason Frank for Salesforce roles; phase out casual agency usage"," ","+14. **Legal Services** — $112,554","+    - Bisley Law ($67,414) + Eurofast International ($18,164) + Visalogic ($11,241) + Virtual Legal Counsel ($4,800) + Pinsent Masons ($4,078) + others ($6,858)","+    - Consolidate to 3-firm panel: Bisley (employment), Pinsent Masons (commercial/tech), Visalogic (immigration); exit remaining 10 small firms","+"," ---"," ","-## Priority 3 — Combined Spend $10K–$50K (5 groups, ~$218,471)","+## Priority Tier 3 — Combined Spend $25K–$100K (Groups 15–17, ~$187,960)"," ","-13. **IT Staffing & Recruitment Agencies** — $78,637","-    - Mason Frank ($38,148) + Technet IT Recruitment ($21,952) + Cedar Recruitment ($18,537)","-    - Consolidate Technet + Cedar to Mason Frank as preferred IT staffing PSL","+15. **4I Advisory — Duplicate Entities** — $83,978","+    - 4I Advisory Services ($71,860) + 4I Management Consulting PL ($12,117)","+    - Same parent brand, two legal registrations — consolidate to single master services agreement"," ","-14. **Finance & FP&A Software** — $74,636","-    - Sage UK Limited ($46,895) + Planful, Inc. ($27,741)","-    - Evaluate Planful against Sage FP&A modules; consolidate to single finance platform","+16. **Work Management & Project Tools** — $76,024","+    - Monday.com/Big Frontier ($66,131) + Trello ($6,674) + Smartsheet ($2,995) + Atlassian ($224)","+    - Standardise on Monday.com; terminate Trello and Smartsheet; roll Atlassian ($224) into Monday.com enterprise plan"," ","-15. **Employee Engagement & Performance SaaS** — $27,126","-    - Peakon APS ($17,108) + PerformancePro ($10,018)","-    - Retain Peakon; consolidate PerformancePro into Peakon or HRIS native modules","+17. **Employee Engagement & Learning** — $27,959","+    - Peakon APS ($17,108) + PerformancePro ($10,018) + Epignosis ($833)","+    - Consolidate to single employee engagement + performance platform; Peakon preferred; evaluate Epignosis vs internal LMS"," ","-16. **Employee Benefits Platform** — $21,804","-    - Sodexo SVC India ($17,810) + Pluxee India ($3,994)","-    - Pluxee is rebranded Sodexo Benefits; verify post-spin-off; deduplicate if same entity","+---"," ","-17. **Integration & Automation Platform** — $16,268","-    - Workato Inc. ($16,101) + Zapier Inc. ($167)","-    - Retain Workato (enterprise iPaaS); migrate Zapier automations to Workato, terminate Zapier","+## Priority Tier 4 — Combined Spend < $25K (Groups 18–23, ~$58,271)"," ","----","+18. **Corporate Secretarial / Entity Mgmt** — $17,768","+    - Acclime Corporate Services ($5,413) + Acclime USA ($4,995) + Intertrust Singapore ($7,360)","+    - Consolidate Acclime entities to single global contract; retain Intertrust for Singapore-specific compliance"," ","-## Priority 4 — Combined Spend < $10K (6 groups, ~$33,002)","+19. **Workflow Automation** — $16,268","+    - Workato Inc. ($16,101) + Zapier Inc. ($167)","+    - Retain Workato (enterprise iPaaS); migrate Zapier automations to Workato; terminate Zapier"," ","-18. **Corporate Secretarial — Acclime Duplicate** — $10,408","-    - Acclime Corporate Services ($5,413) + Acclime USA Inc ($4,995)","-    - Same vendor, regional entities; consolidate under global Acclime master agreement","+20. **Developer Tools & Monitoring** — $8,149","+    - JetBrains ($4,083) + Papertrail ($3,900) + Solarwinds ($166)","+    - Retain JetBrains + Papertrail; assess Solarwinds overlap with Papertrail; consolidate if duplicated"," ","-19. **Apple Hardware — 4 AP Entities** — $8,256","-    - Apple Retail UK ($3,548) + Apple Pty Ltd ($2,031) + Apple Distribution International ($1,913) + Apple-Amer ($764)","-    - Consolidate all four to single Apple Business Manager account","+21. **Apple Hardware — Multi-Entity** — $8,256","+    - Apple Retail UK ($3,548) + Apple Pty ($2,031) + Apple Distribution Int'l ($1,913) + Apple AMER ($764)","+    - Consolidate all four to single Apple Business Manager account; single contract for hardware purchasing"," ","-20. **Allianz Insurance — Duplicate Policy** — $7,069","+22. **Allianz Insurance — Duplicate Entities** — $7,069","     - Allianz Australia Workers' Comp ($6,099) + Allianz WA ($971)","-    - Same insurer, two policy accounts; merge WA into national Allianz account","+    - Sub-group within Group 6: same insurer, two state policy accounts — merge WA into national Allianz account"," ","-21. **Atlassian / Trello — Same Vendor** — $6,898","-    - Trello ($6,674) + Atlassian Pty Ltd ($224)","-    - Trello is an Atlassian product; fold into Atlassian Cloud subscription","+23. **Occupational Health Croatia — Duplicate Clinics** — $192","+    - Specijalisticka Ordinacija Helena Blazic ($20) + Specijalisticka Ordinacija Ina Kardos ($20) + Ustanova Medicina Rada Dr. Novacki ($20) + Ustanova Zdravstvenu Skrb ($131)","+    - Designate single occupational health provider in Croatia; terminate others"," ","-22. **DHL Courier — Duplicate Account** — $310","-    - DHL ($191) + DHL Express UK ($119)","-    - Duplicate carrier accounts; merge to single DHL master account","-","-23. **Occupational Health Croatia — 3 Clinics** — $61","-    - Specijalisticka (Blazic) ($20) + Specijalisticka (Kardos) ($20) + Ustanova Dr. Novacki ($20)","-    - Designate one as preferred supplier; terminate other two","-"," ---"," ","-## Summary for Step 09","+## Summary Table for Step 09"," "," | Priority | Groups | Combined Spend |"," |---|---|---|","-| P1 (≥$200K) | 6 | $5,401,697 |","-| P2 ($50K–$200K) | 6 | $573,765 |","-| P3 ($10K–$50K) | 5 | $218,471 |","-| P4 (<$10K) | 6 | $33,002 |","-| **TOTAL** | **23** | **~$6,226,935** |","+| P1 (≥$200K) | 7 | $5,668,677 |","+| P2 ($100K–$200K) | 7 | $983,872 |","+| P3 ($25K–$100K) | 3 | $187,960 |","+| P4 (<$25K) | 6 | $58,271 |","+| **TOTAL** | **23** | **~$6,899,005** |"," ","-Key insight for Step 09: CRM alone = $3.15M (51% of in-scope spend). Duplicate AP entity cleanup (Navan, HR Solution, Acclime, AWS, Bupa, Allianz, Tmforum, Atlassian, DHL, Croatia clinics) = ~$138K zero-negotiation savings from AP hygiene alone.","+Key insight for Step 09: CRM alone = $3.16M (45.8% of in-scope spend). Duplicate AP entity cleanup (Navan, HRSolution, Acclime, AWS, Bupa, Allianz, Apple, DHL) = ~$110K zero-negotiation savings from AP hygiene alone."]}],"originalFile":"---\nname: STEP 07 Consolidation Opportunity Analysis\ndescription: STEP 07 results - 23 duplicate vendor category groups across 4 priority tiers, ~$6.23M spend in scope; CRM is #1 at $3.15M; use in STEP 09 strategy recommendations\ntype: project\n---\n\nSTEP 07 identified 23 consolidation opportunity groups. Total spend in scope: ~$6,226,935 across 386 vendors.\n\n**Why:** Vendor master has duplicate AP entities, same-vendor product overlap, functional platform duplication, and unchecked agency/office proliferation.\n**How to apply:** Reference these groups in STEP 09 strategy recommendations. P1 groups (>=200K) are immediate CFO-level actions; P2/P3 feed the 90-day vendor review roadmap; P4 is hygiene cleanup.\n\n---\n\n## Priority 1 — Combined Spend ≥ $200K (6 groups, ~$5,401,697)\n\n1. **CRM & Marketing Automation** — $3,151,402\n   - Salesforce UK ($3,117,226) + HubSpot Ireland ($32,187) + Slack Technologies ($1,989)\n   - Retain Salesforce; consolidate Slack via Salesforce EA; evaluate HubSpot overlap with Salesforce Marketing Cloud\n\n2. **Flexible Office Space / Coworking** — $955,652\n   - TOG UK ($263,821) + Zagrebtower ($183,754) + Innovent Spaces ($147,348) + Weking ($144,093) + GPT Space ($133,507) + WeWork Singapore ($64,373) + Work Easy ($14,913) + Common Desk ($3,842)\n   - Retain TOG (London), Innovent (India), Zagrebtower (Croatia) as regional anchors; exit GPT Space, WeWork, Weking, Work Easy, Common Desk\n\n3. **Audit, Accounting & Finance Advisory** — $533,422\n   - BDO LLP ($343,081) + RSM UK Corporate Finance ($117,078) + Grant Thornton ($46,539) + Collards ($12,879) + PwC ($4,879) + Crowe Horwath ($4,062) + McBurneys ($2,711) + N S Shastri ($2,194)\n   - Retain BDO (primary) + RSM (secondary); redirect all other firms to BDO/RSM panel; terminate standalone smaller firms\n\n4. **T&E Platform — Navan Duplicate** — $415,913\n   - Navan (TripActions Inc) ($357,984) + Navan Inc ($57,929)\n   - Same vendor, two AP entities; merge Navan Inc into TripActions master; renegotiate on combined $416K volume\n\n5. **Cloud Infrastructure** — $415,508\n   - Cloudcrossing BVBA ($208,675) + AWS LLC ($106,399) + Cloud Technology Solutions ($60,661) + Google Ireland ($24,798) + Microsoft Ireland ($9,822) + AWS Inc. ($5,153)\n   - Merge AWS Inc. into AWS LLC org billing; evaluate CTS vs Cloudcrossing scope overlap; audit Azure vs AWS allocation\n\n6. **Group Health Insurance** — $339,918\n   - Aetna Life & Casualty ($124,661) + Jensten Insurance ($142,700) + Care Health ($24,045) + Bupa-Supplier ($22,800) + Cigna SG ($13,249) + Bupa Australia ($12,463)\n   - Consolidate Bupa Australia into Bupa-Supplier; benchmark Aetna at renewal; rationalise to max 2–3 global providers\n\n---\n\n## Priority 2 — Combined Spend $50K–$200K (6 groups, ~$573,765)\n\n7. **Telecom & Connectivity** — $129,982\n   - Telefonica Global Services GmbH ($89,880) + Hrvatski Telekom ($18,084) + Telefonica Compras Electronicas ($6,157) + Telemach Hrvatska ($5,134) + Vodafone AU ($3,672) + T-Mobile ($3,357) + Starhub ($2,205) + British Telecom ($1,493)\n   - Retain Telefonica Global GmbH as primary; merge Telefonica Compras into GmbH; retain regional carriers only where no Telefonica coverage\n\n8. **M&A Advisory & Deal Services** — $109,854\n   - SS&C Intralinks ($39,966) + Houlihan Lokey ($37,461) + Vector Capital ($32,427)\n   - Deal-specific spend; verify ongoing engagement; terminate post-deal if activity complete\n\n9. **Digital & Performance Marketing Agencies** — $102,247\n   - Big Frontier/Cult of Monday ($66,131) + Mightyhive ($19,042) + Plus Your Business ($17,074)\n   - Retain Big Frontier as lead agency; consolidate Mightyhive + Plus Your Business mandates into Big Frontier\n\n10. **HR Services — Duplicate Entity** — $87,810\n    - HR Solution International GmbH ($80,823) + HRsolution International AG ($6,987)\n    - Same vendor, two legal entities; merge AG into GmbH master agreement\n\n11. **Sales Intelligence & Prospecting** — $85,801\n    - LinkedIn Ireland ($55,573) + Cognism ($27,013) + Lusha ($2,606) + Dun & Bradstreet ($610)\n    - Retain LinkedIn + Cognism; terminate Lusha and D&B (overlapping, lower-tier tools)\n\n12. **TM Forum — Duplicate AP Entry** — $58,071\n    - Tmforum ($57,560) + Tm Forum ($510)\n    - Same association, duplicate AP records; deduplicate to single entry immediately\n\n---\n\n## Priority 3 — Combined Spend $10K–$50K (5 groups, ~$218,471)\n\n13. **IT Staffing & Recruitment Agencies** — $78,637\n    - Mason Frank ($38,148) + Technet IT Recruitment ($21,952) + Cedar Recruitment ($18,537)\n    - Consolidate Technet + Cedar to Mason Frank as preferred IT staffing PSL\n\n14. **Finance & FP&A Software** — $74,636\n    - Sage UK Limited ($46,895) + Planful, Inc. ($27,741)\n    - Evaluate Planful against Sage FP&A modules; consolidate to single finance platform\n\n15. **Employee Engagement & Performance SaaS** — $27,126\n    - Peakon APS ($17,108) + PerformancePro ($10,018)\n    - Retain Peakon; consolidate PerformancePro into Peakon or HRIS native modules\n\n16. **Employee Benefits Platform** — $21,804\n    - Sodexo SVC India ($17,810) + Pluxee India ($3,994)\n    - Pluxee is rebranded Sodexo Benefits; verify post-spin-off; deduplicate if same entity\n\n17. **Integration & Automation Platform** — $16,268\n    - Workato Inc. ($16,101) + Zapier Inc. ($167)\n    - Retain Workato (enterprise iPaaS); migrate Zapier automations to Workato, terminate Zapier\n\n---\n\n## Priority 4 — Combined Spend < $10K (6 groups, ~$33,002)\n\n18. **Corporate Secretarial — Acclime Duplicate** — $10,408\n    - Acclime Corporate Services ($5,413) + Acclime USA Inc ($4,995)\n    - Same vendor, regional entities; consolidate under global Acclime master agreement\n\n19. **Apple Hardware — 4 AP Entities** — $8,256\n    - Apple Retail UK ($3,548) + Apple Pty Ltd ($2,031) + Apple Distribution International ($1,913) + Apple-Amer ($764)\n    - Consolidate all four to single Apple Business Manager account\n\n20. **Allianz Insurance — Duplicate Policy** — $7,069\n    - Allianz Australia Workers' Comp ($6,099) + Allianz WA ($971)\n    - Same insurer, two policy accounts; merge WA into national Allianz account\n\n21. **Atlassian / Trello — Same Vendor** — $6,898\n    - Trello ($6,674) + Atlassian Pty Ltd ($224)\n    - Trello is an Atlassian product; fold into Atlassian Cloud subscription\n\n22. **DHL Courier — Duplicate Account** — $310\n    - DHL ($191) + DHL Express UK ($119)\n    - Duplicate carrier accounts; merge to single DHL master account\n\n23. **Occupational Health Croatia — 3 Clinics** — $61\n    - Specijalisticka (Blazic) ($20) + Specijalisticka (Kardos) ($20) + Ustanova Dr. Novacki ($20)\n    - Designate one as preferred supplier; terminate other two\n\n---\n\n## Summary for Step 09\n\n| Priority | Groups | Combined Spend |\n|---|---|---|\n| P1 (≥$200K) | 6 | $5,401,697 |\n| P2 ($50K–$200K) | 6 | $573,765 |\n| P3 ($10K–$50K) | 5 | $218,471 |\n| P4 (<$10K) | 6 | $33,002 |\n| **TOTAL** | **23** | **~$6,226,935** |\n\nKey insight for Step 09: CRM alone = $3.15M (51% of in-scope spend). Duplicate AP entity cleanup (Navan, HR Solution, Acclime, AWS, Bupa, Allianz, Tmforum, Atlassian, DHL, Croatia clinics) = ~$138K zero-negotiation savings from AP hygiene alone.\n"}}
