s flagged; 9 Score-4 vendors need Consolidate→Optimize upgrade; use in STEP 09\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":5,"oldLines":5,"newStart":5,"newLines":5,"lines":[" - [project_vendor_spend_analysis.md](project_vendor_spend_analysis.md) — STEP 03 vendor spend analysis results (top 10, spend tiers, key observations); use in STEP 09 strategy recommendations"," - [project_step02_template_constraints.md](project_step02_template_constraints.md) — STEP 02 template constraints from workbook worksheets; CEO/CFO memo max 1 page + Google Doc link required"," - [project_step06_rationale.md](project_step06_rationale.md) — STEP 06 decision rationale for all 386 vendors (Optimize/Consolidate/Terminate); top-3 opportunities pre-sized for STEP 09","-- [project_step07_consolidation.md](project_step07_consolidation.md) — STEP 07 consolidation analysis: 23 opportunity groups, ~$6.23M combined spend in scope across 4 priority tiers; CRM ($3.15M) is #1; use in STEP 09","+- [project_step07_consolidation.md](project_step07_consolidation.md) — STEP 07 consolidation analysis: 23 opportunity groups, ~$6.89M combined spend in scope across 4 priority tiers; CRM ($3.16M) is #1; use in STEP 09"," - [project_step08_strategic_scores.md](project_step08_strategic_scores.md) — STEP 08 strategic scores (1–5) for all 386 vendors, 187 conflicts flagged; 9 Score-4 vendors need Consolidate→Optimize upgrade; use in STEP 09"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JZqAmLqHwjeAJs4XMGNKAb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the full **STEP 07 — Consolidation Opportunity Analysis** across all 386 vendors:\n\n---\n\n## Consolidation Opportunity Analysis\n**23 groups | 118 vendor entries | $6,899,005 combined spend in scope**\n\n---\n\n### PRIORITY TIER 1 — ≥ $200K (Groups 1–7)\n\n| # | Category | Vendors in Category | Combined Spend | Consolidation Candidate(s) |\n|---|----------|--------------------|--------------:|---------------------------|\n| 1 | **CRM & Sales Engagement** | Salesforce UK ($3,117,226), Cognism ($27,013), Outreach Corp ($9,206), Lusha ($2,606), Dun & Bradstreet ($610) | **$3,156,660** | Retain Salesforce as core; consolidate Cognism/Outreach/Lusha into Salesforce-native Sales Intelligence or a single prospecting tool — ~$39K direct overlap |\n| 2 | **Office Space & Real Estate** | TOG UK Properties ($263,821), Zagrebtower ($183,754), Innovent Spaces ($147,348), GPT Space & Co ($133,507), WeWork Singapore ($64,373), Jones Lang LaSalle ($16,274), Work Easy Solutions ($14,913), Common Desk ($3,842) | **$827,834** | Appoint JLL as single strategic real estate manager; exit underutilised co-working (GPT Space, WeWork, Work Easy, Common Desk); retain TOG (London), Innovent (India), Zagrebtower (Croatia) as regional anchors |\n| 3 | **Travel & Expense — Navan Duplicate** | Navan/TripActions Inc ($357,984), Navan Inc ($57,929) | **$415,913** | **IMMEDIATE** — same vendor, two AP billing entities; consolidate to single Navan contract and renegotiate on combined $416K volume |\n| 4 | **Audit & Accounting** | BDO LLP ($343,081), Grant Thornton ($46,539), Granttree Limited ($13,659), PricewaterhouseCoopers ($4,879), Crowe Horwath Revizija ($4,062) | **$412,219** | Retain BDO as primary statutory auditor; consolidate advisory mandates to BDO; retain Granttree for R&D tax credits only; exit PwC and Crowe Horwath |\n| 5 | **Cloud Infrastructure** | Cloudcrossing BVBA ($208,675), AWS LLC ($106,399), Cloud Technology Solutions ($60,661), Microsoft Ireland ($9,822), AWS Inc. ($5,153) | **$390,710** | Consolidate AWS LLC + AWS Inc. to single AWS contract (duplicate AP entities); clarify Cloudcrossing scope vs. native AWS managed services; define AWS vs. Azure cloud strategy |\n| 6 | **Employee Health Insurance** | Aetna ($124,661), Agram Life ($24,952), Care Health Insurance ($24,045), Bupa-Supplier ($22,800), Cigna SG ($13,249), Bupa Australia ($12,463), Allianz AU Workers' Comp ($6,099), ICICI Lombard ($5,972), Cici Prudential ($3,195), Allianz WA ($971) | **$238,406** | Merge Bupa-Supplier + Bupa Australia into single Bupa contract; merge Allianz AU + WA (see Group 22); engage global benefits broker to coordinate regional policies |\n| 7 | **Financial & M&A Advisory** | RSM UK Corporate Finance ($117,078), SS&C Intralinks ($39,966), Houlihan Lokey ($37,461), Vector Capital ($32,427) | **$226,932** | Consolidate VDR to SS&C Intralinks; rationalise M&A advisory to preferred panel; verify post-deal ongoing need for Vector Capital and Houlihan Lokey |\n\n---\n\n### PRIORITY TIER 2 — $100K–$200K (Groups 8–14)\n\n| # | Category | Vendors in Category | Combined Spend | Consolidation Candidate(s) |\n|---|----------|--------------------|--------------:|---------------------------|\n| 8 | **HR Outsourcing & Payroll** | HR Solution Int'l GmbH ($80,823), Harmonic Group ($65,418), HRSolution Int'l AG ($6,987), Mercer Limited ($5,444), NCC Services ($3,036) | **$161,708** | **Immediate:** consolidate HRSolution GmbH + AG (same brand, two legal entities); evaluate Harmonic vs. HRSolution geographic overlap; target single global HR/payroll vendor |\n| 9 | **Marketing Automation & Digital Advertising** | LinkedIn Ireland ($55,573), HubSpot Ireland ($32,187), Uberflip ($26,091), Google Ireland ($24,798), MightyHive ($19,042), Semrush ($3,730) | **$161,420** | Retain HubSpot as primary marketing automation; evaluate Uberflip vs. HubSpot Content Hub (likely overlap); rationalise MightyHive as managed agency layer |\n| 10 | **Insurance Brokerage** | Jensten Insurance Brokers ($142,700), Shoff Darby Companies ($10,100) | **$152,800** | Consolidate to single broker; Jensten as primary; negotiate combined policy portfolio discount |\n| 11 | **Telecoms & Connectivity** | Telefonica Global ($89,880), New Star Networks ($23,887), Hrvatski Telekom ($18,084), Telemach Hrvatska ($5,134), Vodafone AU ($3,672), T-Mobile ($3,357), Starhub SG ($2,205), British Telecom ($1,493) | **$147,712** | Retain Telefonica Global as primary telco; rationalise Croatian connectivity — choose one of Hrvatski Telekom vs. Telemach; consolidate regional mobile contracts |\n| 12 | **Financial Planning SaaS** | Kimble Applications ($52,825), Sage UK ($46,895), Planful ($27,741) | **$127,462** | Retain Sage for statutory accounting; evaluate Kimble (PSA/resource planning) vs. Planful (FP&A) for functional overlap; consolidate finance planning to one platform |\n| 13 | **Recruitment & Staffing Agencies** | Accutrainee ($38,841), Mason Frank ($38,148), Technet IT Recruitment ($21,952), Cedar Recruitment ($18,537), Info Edge India ($3,536) | **$121,014** | Establish preferred supplier list of 2–3 agencies; Mason Frank for Salesforce/tech roles; consolidate or eliminate casual agency usage across Accutrainee, Technet, Cedar |\n| 14 | **Legal Services** | Bisley Law ($67,414), Eurofast International ($18,164), Visalogic ($11,241), Virtual Legal Counsel ($4,800), Pinsent Masons ($4,078), Curzon Green ($1,158), Quadrant Law ($1,327), Thomas Mansfield ($1,135), Lane IP ($852), Franklin Gringer ($427), Kilgannon & Partners ($681), KLG Kalra Legal ($681), Induslaw ($596) | **$112,554** | Consolidate to 3-firm panel: Bisley Law (employment), Pinsent Masons (commercial/tech), Visalogic (immigration); exit remaining 10 ad-hoc firms |\n\n---\n\n### PRIORITY TIER 3 — $25K–$100K (Groups 15–17)\n\n| # | Category | Vendors in Category | Combined Spend | Consolidation Candidate(s) |\n|---|----------|--------------------|--------------:|---------------------------|\n| 15 | **4I Advisory — Duplicate Entities** | 4I Advisory Services ($71,860), 4I Management Consulting PL ($12,117) | **$83,978** | Same parent brand registered as two legal entities — consolidate to single master services agreement immediately |\n| 16 | **Work Management & Project Tools** | Monday.com/Big Frontier ($66,131), Trello ($6,674), Smartsheet ($2,995), Atlassian ($224) | **$76,024** | Standardise on Monday.com as primary; terminate Trello and Smartsheet; evaluate Atlassian for dev-specific use only |\n| 17 | **Employee Engagement & Learning** | Peakon APS ($17,108), PerformancePro ($10,018), Epignosis ($833) | **$27,959** | Consolidate to single platform; retain Peakon (engagement + surveys); consolidate PerformancePro into Peakon or HRIS native performance modules |\n\n---\n\n### PRIORITY TIER 4 — < $25K / AP Hygiene (Groups 18–23)\n\n| # | Category | Vendors in Category | Combined Spend | Consolidation Candidate(s) |\n|---|----------|--------------------|--------------:|---------------------------|\n| 18 | **Corporate Secretarial** | Acclime Corporate Services ($5,413), Acclime USA ($4,995), Intertrust Singapore ($7,360) | **$17,768** | Consolidate Acclime entities to single global master agreement; retain Intertrust for Singapore-specific compliance |\n| 19 | **Workflow Automation** | Workato Inc. ($16,101), Zapier Inc. ($167) | **$16,268** | Retain Workato (enterprise iPaaS); migrate Zapier automations; terminate Zapier |\n| 20 | **Developer Tools & Monitoring** | JetBrains ($4,083), Papertrail ($3,900), Solarwinds ($166) | **$8,149** | Retain JetBrains + Papertrail; assess Solarwinds overlap with Papertrail log management |\n| 21 | **Apple Hardware — Multi-Entity** | Apple Retail UK ($3,548), Apple Pty Ltd ($2,031), Apple Distribution Int'l ($1,913), Apple AMER ($764) | **$8,256** | Consolidate all four AP entities to single Apple Business Manager account |\n| 22 | **Allianz Insurance — Duplicate Entities** | Allianz Australia Workers' Comp ($6,099), Allianz WA ($971) | **$7,069** | Sub-group of Group 6 — same insurer, two state policy accounts; merge WA into national Allianz policy |\n| 23 | **Occupational Health Croatia — Duplicates** | Spec. Ordinacija Helena Blazic ($20), Spec. Ordinacija Ina Kardos ($20), Ustanova Medicina Rada Dr. Novacki ($20), Ustanova Zdravstvenu Skrb PP ($131) | **$192** | Designate one clinic as preferred occupational health provider; terminate the other three |\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Priority Tier | Groups | Combined Spend |\n|---|:---:|--------------:|\n| P1 — ≥$200K | 7 | $5,668,677 |\n| P2 — $100K–$200K | 7 | $983,872 |\n| P3 — $25K–$100K | 3 | $187,960 |\n| P4 — <$25K (AP hygiene) | 6 | $58,271 |\n| **TOTAL** | **23** | **$6,899,005** |\n\n**Key observations for STEP 09:**\n- **CRM alone = $3.16M (45.8% of in-scope spend)** — all consolidation leverage here sits in rationalising the Salesforce satellite tools (~$39K), not replacing Salesforce.\n- **AP entity duplicates** (Navan, HRSolution, AWS, Acclime, Bupa, Allianz, Apple) = ~$110K in zero-negotiation savings from pure AP hygiene.\n- **Quick wins in P1:** Groups 3 (Navan), 4 (Audit), and 5 (Cloud) require no new contracts — they're billing entity rationalisation and incumbent renegotiation.\n\nMemory updated with fresh figures for use in STEP 09."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":337,"cache_read_input_tokens":64667,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":337,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ed88350-d5e8-4179-8856-45e53162fa46","uuid":"a26e1051-6f96-4a1c-947f-3504036b7737"}
